{{no footnotes|date=October 2016}}
'''''Kildare'''''   is an un-powered butty boat constructed of riveted iron. It was built around 1913 by Braithwaite & Kirk of West Bromwich to be towed behind a powered craft like President. It is complete with a fully fitted boatman’s living cabin and traditional covering cloths over the main hold area.
It is now owned by the [[Black Country Living Museum]], where it is based and can be seen dockside in the Lord Ward’s Canal Arm at the [[Black Country Living Museum]] in Dudley when she is not out on the canal system with [[President (narrowboat)|'' President '']].
Boat is maintained and operated by Friends of President on behalf of the Black Country Living Museum.
Kildare is on the [[National Historic Ships|'' National Historic Ships]] register.

